  more convenient to update JSON fields. The Markdown with frontmatter can be generated dynamically just for the REST API endpoint response. E.g.
  Store structure: { "id": "...", name: "...", "description": "", "status": "...", "contractAddress": "...", "chainId": "...", "content": "..." }
  Output examples:
  { "status": "failed", "content": "<error-message>" }
  { "status": "processing", "content": "<some-helpful-information>" }
  { "status": "ready", "content", "<full-markdown-content-with-frontmatter" }
  What do you think?

